{{Taxobox | name = ''Bacillus'' phage G | image = | image_caption = | virus_group = i | ordo = ''[[Caudovirales]]'' | familia = ''[[Myoviridae]]'' | genus = Unassigned | species = ''Bacillus'' phage G }}
'''''Bacillus'' phage G''' is a [[bacteriophage]] (phage) that infects ''[[Bacillus]]'' bacteria. The phage has been reported to have the largest [[genome]] of all discovered ''Myoviridae'' with nearly 700 protein-coding genes.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Kristensen|first=DM|author2=Cai X|author3=Mushegian A|title=Evolutionarily conserved orthologous families in phages are relatively rare in their prokaryotic hosts|journal=J Bacteriol|date=Apr 2011|volume=193|issue=8|pages=1806–14|doi=10.1128/JB.01311-10|pmid=21317336|pmc=3133016}}</ref>
