The term "'''down to fuck'''" ('''DTF''') is slang for a person willing to have sexual intercourse (or [[fuck]]) with another person, often in the form of [[casual sex]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DTF|url=http://neologisms.rice.edu/index.php?a=term&d=1&t=9370|publisher=The Rice University Neologisms Database|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> The term has been in use since 2007 having been mentioned in the film ''[[Superbad (film)|Superbad]]'' and has been widely used in the media, movies, and music. It was a catchphrase used by [[Michael Sorrentino|Mike "The Situation" Sorrentino]] on the ''[[Jersey Shore (TV series)|Jersey Shore]]''.<ref>{{cite book|editor1-last=Victor|editor1-first=Terry|editor2-last=Dalzell|editor2-first=Tom|title=The Concise New Partridge Dictionary of Slang and Unconventional English|date=2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317625124|page=266|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h0mcBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA266&lpg=PA266&dq=down+to+fuck+dtf+2008&source=bl&ots=_KtNW-mP_i&sig=59-vQmofF_1YZF_2uA1vnY_bwow&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjf8ouG_-raAhXpLMAKHXVrBmkQ6AEISjAE#v=onepage&q=down%20to%20fuck%20dtf%202008&f=false|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Rensin|first1=Emmett|last2=Aciman|first2=Alexander|title=Twitterature: The World's Greatest Books in Twenty Tweets or Less|date=2009|publisher=Penguin|isbn=9781101162828|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=p9KKxifhvnIC&pg=PT185&dq=down+to+fuck+dtf&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwit_9mi_uraAhWIDsAKHdg7DvQQ6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=down%20to%20fuck%20dtf&f=false|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Seth Rogen on Twitter|url=https://twitter.com/Sethrogen/status/898372399703445505?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hollywoodreporter.com%2Fnews%2Fseth-rogen-drops-superbad-trivia-10-year-anniversary-1030822&tfw_creator=THR&tfw_site=THR|publisher=Twitter|date=August 17, 2017|quote=The cast of Jersey Shore confirmed to me that the phrase "D.T.F" or "Down To Fuck" is from Superbad.|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Desta|first1=Yohana|title=Of Course Superbad Was the First Movie to Use This Perfectly Gross Curse Word|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/08/superbad-anniversary-seth-rogen|publisher=Vanity Fair|date=August 18, 2017|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>

