'''Paula (Kellner) Arnold''' ({{lang-he|ארנולד, פאולה}}; 1885-1968) was an Austrian-born Israeli [[journalist]], [[botanist]], and [[naturalist]] noted for her works on the flora and birds of Israel.<ref>{{cite web |title=Paula Arnold |url=https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/paula-arnold |website=www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org |accessdate=16 September 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Encyclopaedia Judaica. |date=1971 |publisher=Encyclopaedia Judaica ; Macmillan |page=10:308 |url=http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/242475 |accessdate=16 September 2018}}</ref>

